WEBVTT

00:06.840 --> 00:08.440
[Squawks]

00:08.480 --> 00:11.080
Narrator:
Previously on "Meerkat Manor,"

00:11.120 --> 00:13.840
Flint was under pressure,

00:13.880 --> 00:16.080
keeping her hakuna matata family

00:16.120 --> 00:18.760
out of harm's way.

00:18.800 --> 00:22.520
While Whiskers boy Lylook
cast a roving eye

00:22.560 --> 00:27.000
over her younger sisters.

00:27.040 --> 00:31.560
And Swift's new pups
emerged from the burrow

00:31.600 --> 00:34.080
for the very first time.

00:34.120 --> 00:38.160
♪

00:38.200 --> 00:40.280
[MUSIC]

00:55.040 --> 00:56.720
[THUNDER CLAPS]

01:24.040 --> 01:26.720
[SQUEAKING]

01:29.920 --> 01:33.560
They say that home
is where the heart is.

01:35.280 --> 01:38.720
But a home must also
provide protection

01:38.760 --> 01:40.920
and the means to survive.

01:44.440 --> 01:46.800
When either are lacking,

01:46.840 --> 01:49.160
or fate forces your hand,

01:51.000 --> 01:55.680
sometimes your only choice
is to move on.

02:02.960 --> 02:05.560
[BIRDS SING]

02:12.920 --> 02:15.280
[MEERKATS SQUEAK]

02:21.440 --> 02:23.120
[BIRDS SING]

02:23.160 --> 02:25.880
Dawn marks the start
of a new adventure

02:25.920 --> 02:27.640
at the Whisker's burrow.

02:31.840 --> 02:34.200
[SQUEAKS]

02:34.240 --> 02:38.000
It's time for the youngest
members, Laika, Hachi and Fly

02:38.040 --> 02:41.240
to experience life
beyond the burrow.

02:59.120 --> 03:02.600
Everybody is itching
to get out and escort them

03:02.640 --> 03:04.320
on this important occasion...

03:06.200 --> 03:11.200
No one more so than their
mother, family matriarch Swift.

03:12.360 --> 03:13.760
[SCRATCHES]

03:13.800 --> 03:16.800
Itching being
the operative word.

03:21.520 --> 03:23.080
One of the downsides

03:23.120 --> 03:27.360
of staying put in a nursery
burrow for more than a month

03:27.400 --> 03:31.720
is it becomes increasingly
infested with parasites.

03:39.320 --> 03:42.880
No amount of housework
is going to fix this.

03:45.640 --> 03:47.520
It's time to quit...

03:47.560 --> 03:49.040
the flea pit.

03:53.480 --> 03:58.080
When everyone's ready,
the family set off.

04:05.760 --> 04:10.080
They don't get very far before
hunger gets the better of them.

04:11.640 --> 04:13.280
[SQUAWKS]

04:14.920 --> 04:17.680
Keeping watch
as everyone tucks in

04:17.720 --> 04:20.440
is unlucky-in-love, Lilac.

04:23.800 --> 04:26.720
After his failed attempt
at roving,

04:26.760 --> 04:29.080
he's back home with mum and dad.

04:32.640 --> 04:36.080
He may need more practice
attracting girls,

04:36.120 --> 04:38.680
but he's an old hand
at sentry duty.

04:42.920 --> 04:47.000
And he'll do everything he can
to protect his baby sisters.

04:48.680 --> 04:50.880
[SQUEAKS]

04:50.920 --> 04:52.480
At five weeks old,

04:52.520 --> 04:56.200
they're now ready for their
first lesson in bug-hunting.

04:57.720 --> 05:00.240
[SQUEAKS]

05:00.280 --> 05:04.880
Step one:
observe your older siblings.

05:06.800 --> 05:10.160
Big sister Bones
has an impressive technique.

05:15.200 --> 05:17.320
Hachi gets the idea,

05:17.360 --> 05:20.280
but discovers that
it's not as easy as it looks.

05:26.120 --> 05:30.240
It seems that success is
relative to size and strength.

05:30.280 --> 05:33.200
[MEERKATS SQUAWK]

05:37.280 --> 05:39.600
Laika takes
a different approach.

05:43.120 --> 05:46.240
One that requires
a lot less effort.

05:48.440 --> 05:51.480
That juicy gecko looks big
enough for two.

05:52.760 --> 05:54.680
[LOUD SQUAWKS]

05:58.200 --> 06:01.680
Bones turns out
to be a soft touch

06:01.720 --> 06:03.320
and gives her the whole thing.

06:06.680 --> 06:09.520
That should keep her little
sister quiet for a while.

06:18.600 --> 06:22.840
After the pitstop,
Swift is eager to get going.

06:25.640 --> 06:27.000
The wind is picking up,

06:27.040 --> 06:30.400
making it harder
to smell or hear predators.

06:33.280 --> 06:34.880
For everyone's safety

06:34.920 --> 06:38.880
she needs to keep her family
close and keep them moving.

06:42.160 --> 06:46.520
Partner Brea
will bring up the rear,

06:46.560 --> 06:49.880
his eyes may be old but
he won't leave anyone behind.

06:53.960 --> 06:56.680
Swift pushes on,

06:56.720 --> 07:01.600
she must find a new home for
her family before the sun sets.

07:04.680 --> 07:06.960
[BIRDS SING]

07:23.000 --> 07:24.560
Across the Manor,

07:24.600 --> 07:28.160
another mother is leading
her family through the desert.

07:31.600 --> 07:36.520
Hakuna Matata's dominant female
Flint Lockwood is...

07:36.560 --> 07:39.560
pregnant again...

07:39.600 --> 07:43.400
but she's struggling to provide
for the pups she's already got.

07:45.720 --> 07:49.680
There's little in the way
of cooling breeze here.

07:49.720 --> 07:54.280
And in her small, parched
territory, pickings are slim.

07:59.160 --> 08:02.400
Three-month-old Azizi
is no longer a novice hunter...

08:04.200 --> 08:06.080
there's just nothing here.

08:10.400 --> 08:12.320
Everybody's feeling the pinch,

08:14.160 --> 08:17.400
and it's Flint's job
to solve the problem.

08:19.040 --> 08:23.080
She also needs to consider
her unborn pups.

08:26.960 --> 08:29.960
Standing at the border
of her territory,

08:30.000 --> 08:32.400
Flint faces a dilemma.

08:37.200 --> 08:39.800
Venturing further
she could lead her family

08:39.840 --> 08:42.000
to a more secure future...

08:47.560 --> 08:51.440
But if they trespass
onto a rival family's patch,

08:51.480 --> 08:53.960
she could land them
in serious trouble.

08:57.160 --> 08:59.280
Crossing into potential
enemy territory

08:59.320 --> 09:03.800
is the ultimate test of courage
for any leader.

09:03.840 --> 09:07.080
For one so inexperienced,
and pregnant,

09:07.120 --> 09:09.560
it's a risky move indeed.

09:12.320 --> 09:15.880
But Flint does have
one potential asset.

09:20.120 --> 09:24.000
New partner, Finnick.

09:24.040 --> 09:27.880
Though quite the family man now,
before hooking up with Flint,

09:27.920 --> 09:30.280
he led a bachelor's life...

09:31.760 --> 09:34.360
roving all over the manor.

09:38.480 --> 09:40.240
His navigational know-how

09:40.280 --> 09:43.840
could be just what this
over-stretched mum needs.

09:49.000 --> 09:53.000
But can she rely on Finnick to
lead them all to a better life?

10:02.680 --> 10:08.800
As they cross into the unknown,
Flint is about to find out.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.680
On the Whiskers' side
of the manor,

10:29.720 --> 10:32.520
the pups have now travelled
quite a distance.

10:36.440 --> 10:40.120
The blustery wind is making it
hard to hear warning calls...

10:42.680 --> 10:44.880
and everyone's getting
a little jumpy.

10:50.040 --> 10:50.920
Suddenly...

10:50.960 --> 10:52.720
[ALARM CALL]

10:52.760 --> 10:54.440
Lilac sounds an alarm.

10:59.200 --> 11:01.400
But instead of
bolting for cover,

11:01.440 --> 11:03.760
nobody seems to know what to do.

11:06.080 --> 11:08.880
It's not clear
what kind of danger.

11:14.560 --> 11:16.360
Is it a bird of prey?

11:18.640 --> 11:20.400
Or something on the ground?

11:25.120 --> 11:27.120
Molerat joins Lilac

11:27.160 --> 11:29.960
to see if he can decipher
what the problem is.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.720
Then he spots it.

11:41.760 --> 11:43.160
[ALARM CALL]

11:44.280 --> 11:47.200
A solitary figure 30 yards away.

11:49.160 --> 11:51.920
[FRANTIC SQUEAKS]

11:51.960 --> 11:54.600
There's no question
what the threat is now.

11:57.240 --> 11:59.960
The stranger may be alone

12:00.000 --> 12:02.320
but if he's got his family
with him,

12:02.360 --> 12:05.240
this could turn into
a territorial battle...

12:06.680 --> 12:09.640
...with the weakest
picked off first.

12:14.880 --> 12:16.440
It's everyone for themselves

12:16.480 --> 12:18.760
as they search
for somewhere to hide.

12:21.480 --> 12:23.400
But where IS the enemy now?

12:24.720 --> 12:27.960
In these bushes,
it's impossible to tell.

12:34.560 --> 12:36.920
Lilac finds a bolt hole...

12:38.280 --> 12:39.920
but it turns out to be no entry.

12:44.040 --> 12:47.560
The entrance tunnel has
collapsed, blocking access.

12:51.120 --> 12:55.280
Exposed above ground,
Swift doesn't have many options.

12:57.320 --> 12:59.600
She goes for stealth...

13:01.640 --> 13:06.520
and, using the undergrowth for
cover, leads her family onwards.

13:15.600 --> 13:21.120
She can only hope she is
taking them away from danger.

13:24.520 --> 13:27.000
[WIND BLOWS]

13:30.440 --> 13:32.200
Across the dunes,

13:32.240 --> 13:36.960
Flint's hopes for better fortune
are falling on stony ground.

13:45.320 --> 13:48.160
In the burning heat
of the midday sun,

13:48.200 --> 13:52.000
the pace has dropped
to little more than an amble.

13:54.640 --> 13:57.080
Far from navigating up front,

13:57.120 --> 14:00.480
Finnick seems to be
dawdling at the back...

14:02.760 --> 14:04.360
[SQUAWKS]

14:04.400 --> 14:07.680
...and there's a distinct lack
of discipline in the ranks.

14:10.040 --> 14:12.000
Tired, hot and hungry,

14:12.040 --> 14:15.480
petty squabbles are breaking out
over food.

14:15.520 --> 14:19.280
[SQUAWKING]

14:19.320 --> 14:23.960
Plucky Azizi
wants her dad's lunch.

14:25.560 --> 14:27.360
But he's having none of it.

14:31.160 --> 14:34.600
All this is undermining
Flint's authority.

14:34.640 --> 14:37.120
Time is marching on.

14:37.160 --> 14:39.520
She needs to find a place with
better prospects

14:39.560 --> 14:42.280
for her growing family...

14:42.320 --> 14:45.880
and a new burrow
to eventually give birth in.

14:49.600 --> 14:54.160
The stakes are extremely high
for this inexperienced leader.

15:04.400 --> 15:07.200
After an adrenaline-fuelled
morning,

15:07.240 --> 15:10.680
the Whiskers take a moment
to catch their breaths.

15:13.360 --> 15:15.080
The wind has dropped

15:15.120 --> 15:18.600
and the menacing stranger
seems to have vanished.

15:22.320 --> 15:26.800
Everyone is shaken
but at least they're together.

15:29.600 --> 15:31.520
The pups first day away
from the burrow

15:31.560 --> 15:34.840
is proving to be
unexpectedly arduous

15:36.080 --> 15:38.120
and they are exhausted.

15:40.200 --> 15:43.800
Lilac does his best
to comfort his sisters.

15:50.840 --> 15:55.280
Brea offers
some fatherly reassurance.

15:55.320 --> 15:59.600
All this running around is
taking its toll on his old bones

15:59.640 --> 16:01.760
so he's glad of a rest too.

16:05.560 --> 16:08.760
Swift can't afford
such indulgence.

16:12.320 --> 16:15.600
She has to stay focused
on the task in hand.

16:18.400 --> 16:22.280
So, where to now?

16:22.320 --> 16:25.800
For the sake of her pups,
she'd better have a good plan.

16:39.280 --> 16:42.240
As afternoon
turns to early evening,

16:42.280 --> 16:45.960
time is running out on
Flint's house-hunting mission.

16:50.320 --> 16:56.120
Finnick's dawdling earlier cost
them valuable travelling time.

16:56.160 --> 16:58.760
But his inside track
on the Manor has led them

16:58.800 --> 17:00.480
to a new area...

17:02.240 --> 17:04.800
and... a new burrow.

17:07.720 --> 17:10.000
[PARTY MUSIC]

17:10.040 --> 17:14.160
He wastes no time
scent-marking the dream home.

17:17.320 --> 17:20.520
It's certainly big enough
for the whole family...

17:21.560 --> 17:24.000
And boasts multiple entrances.

17:26.160 --> 17:27.960
Someone's been here before...

17:28.000 --> 17:29.920
but no-one's currently
in residence

17:29.960 --> 17:33.280
and it doesn't look like it
needs any major renovations.

17:38.240 --> 17:40.600
But the menu choices
at the local diner

17:40.640 --> 17:43.480
appear to be rather limited.

17:48.320 --> 17:52.680
And there's an even more
significant drawback.

17:52.720 --> 17:55.880
[CAR ENGINE RUMBLES]

17:57.880 --> 18:00.480
Positioned between two roads,

18:00.520 --> 18:03.720
this place
is a potential death trap.

18:03.760 --> 18:06.760
[CAR RUSHES]

18:06.800 --> 18:09.440
Finnick might
have delivered the best house...

18:09.480 --> 18:11.600
but it's on the worst street.

18:14.680 --> 18:17.280
This is no place
to raise a young family.

18:20.560 --> 18:23.360
Flint's hopes
of finding a perfect home

18:24.320 --> 18:26.160
have yet to materialise.

18:28.240 --> 18:32.760
But for tonight, at least,
it will have to do.

18:46.240 --> 18:47.800
As dusk falls,

18:47.840 --> 18:52.640
it's time for Swift to reveal
her plans for her family.

18:57.280 --> 19:01.160
The pups badly need to get their
heads down for the night.

19:03.120 --> 19:06.480
So where is their
new family home?

19:31.440 --> 19:33.400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:56.440 --> 20:01.160
A derelict water tank
is not your typical Manor house.

20:04.480 --> 20:08.600
And it's hard to fathom
exactly what it has to offer.

20:13.080 --> 20:15.240
They may have to wait
until morning

20:15.280 --> 20:19.000
for this concrete carbuncle
to reveal its potential.

20:21.080 --> 20:25.000
For now, they'll simply have to
trust their leader.

20:37.400 --> 20:39.360
[SCRATCHING]

20:45.120 --> 20:47.600
[DISTANT SQUEAKS]

21:18.880 --> 21:20.600
After a good night's sleep,

21:20.640 --> 21:24.480
the Whiskers are waking up
to their new reality.

21:29.880 --> 21:34.080
A wide-eyed Lilac
has never seen anything like it.

21:36.800 --> 21:40.320
But Swift seems
very much at home.

21:40.360 --> 21:43.960
Was this her intended
destination all along?

21:47.840 --> 21:50.160
It has an excellent
sun terrace...

21:54.600 --> 21:57.280
...and Laika, Hachi and Fly
seem thrilled

21:57.320 --> 21:59.440
with their
adventure playground...

22:01.880 --> 22:05.240
...even if it is very different
from what they're used to.

22:10.040 --> 22:14.840
But just look at that view.

22:27.400 --> 22:30.120
It's not the most conventional
of locations...

22:32.240 --> 22:35.240
but it is abundant with life.

22:38.080 --> 22:39.640
And there can be no doubt

22:39.680 --> 22:43.440
that Swift has done well
bringing her family here.

22:46.200 --> 22:51.200
She has shown a glimpse
of who she really is.

22:51.240 --> 22:55.640
A worthy leader with the wisdom
and courage of her forebears.

22:57.280 --> 23:02.560
In her, the Whiskers dynasty
truly lives on.

23:05.800 --> 23:08.400
But Swift would do well
to remember

23:08.440 --> 23:10.920
that when the Kalahari
gives with one hand,

23:12.000 --> 23:14.040
it can take with another...

23:14.080 --> 23:17.120
[CRASH OF THUNDER]

23:17.160 --> 23:20.160
Even in the most bountiful
paradise,

23:20.200 --> 23:23.720
trouble is never far away...

23:23.760 --> 23:30.120
And every family's fortune
can change in a heartbeat.

23:30.160 --> 23:32.440
[THUNDER CRASHES]

23:38.040 --> 23:41.600
♪

23:41.640 --> 23:43.640
Narrator:
In this Garden of Eden,

23:43.680 --> 23:46.840
life couldn't get much rosier
for the Whiskers.

23:46.880 --> 23:50.640
Across the manor,
it's the land-grabbing Ubuntu.

23:50.680 --> 23:54.160
Daisy's got her eye
on the neighbor's territory,

23:54.200 --> 23:56.640
Hakuna Matata's burrow.

23:56.680 --> 23:59.520
Pregnant Flint Lockwood
has a decision to make --

23:59.560 --> 24:02.840
retreat and surrender her land,
or fight to win it back.

24:02.880 --> 24:04.320
[Chirping]

24:04.360 --> 24:06.640
♪

24:08.400 --> 24:11.360
[MUSIC]
